        <abstract> 
<p>Believes that, in <hi rend="italic">Dicentra</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Fumaria</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Corydalis</hi>, flower structures are related directly to visits from bees. Flower stigmas generally are placed in the path of bees.</p> 
            <p>Has received paper from Wallace on natural selection; has sent abstract of his notions, with Wallace’s paper, to Linnean Society.</p>
        </abstract>
